  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-9 clean)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors scoped-out or not-applicable (acceptable at MRL 2). Confidence in several validation outputs is explicitly low and documented with wide uncertainty bounds; a sensitivity analysis documents which uncertain inputs drive those bounds. The decision accepts the limitation as residual risk with a documented offset rationale.",
